    <div>
      <h1>Count: {props.count}</h1>
      <button onClick={handleIncrementClick}>Increment</button>
      <button onClick={handleDecrementClick}>Decrement</button>
    </div>
  );
}
```
When the user clicks the increment or decrement button, the corresponding action is dispatched to the Redux store, causing the store's state to change. React Redux then automatically re-renders the connected component with the new state.

