```

Both examples make a GET request to the specified URL. The `XMLHttpRequest` example attaches event listeners for the `load` and `error` events, while the `fetch()` example uses Promises to handle success and failure cases. You can modify these examples to make other types of HTTP requests (such as POST or PUT) and include data in the request body.

